{"lemma":"فاسِقٌ","slug":"فاسِقٌ","root":"ف.س.ق","root_slug":"ف-س-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-س-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فاسِق","root":"فسق","pos":"N","occurrence_count":37},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33872"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of فَسَقَ (fasaqa)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"sinful, lewd, debauched, libertine, adulterous"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fornicator, libertine, adulterer"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of فَسَقَ (fasaqa)."},"ipa":["/faː.siq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33872","headword_ar":"فَاسِقٌ","root":"fsq","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Going forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who goes forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"departs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the right way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the way of truth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the limits of the law,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the bounds of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obedience;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disobedient"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh, TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgressing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgressor; unrighteous, sinful, wicked, vitious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immoral;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] mostly applied to one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who has taken upon himself to observe what the law ordains, and has acknowledged its authority, and then fallen short of observance in respect of all,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of some, of its ordinances:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and when the person fundamentally, or utterly, an unbeliever is thus termed, it is because he falls short of observing the ordinance that the intellect renders obligatory on him and that the natural constitution with which he was created in his mother's womb requires to be conceded; hence the believer is contrasted with him in the Kur xxxii. 18; so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAsiqN","text_ar":"فَاسِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a more general term than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfirN","text_ar":"كَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaAlimN","text_ar":"ظَالِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a more general term than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAsiqN","text_ar":"فَاسِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (El-Isbahánee, TA:) accord. to IDrd, (O,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAsiq","text_ar":"فَاسِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is thus called because of his divesting himself, or becoming divested, of good: (O, K:) the word has not been heard in the speech of the people of the Time of Ignorance, (IAar, S, O, Msb, K,) nor in their poetry, (IAar, S, O, K,) though it is an Arabic word, (IAar, S, O, Msb, K,) and a chaste one, and the Kur-án has used it: (IAar, Msb:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasaqapN","text_ar":"فَسَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fus~aAqN","text_ar":"فُسَّاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAsiqu","text_ar":"فَوَاسِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAsiqapN","text_ar":"فَاسِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] applied to women, signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAjiru","text_ar":"فَوَاجِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[generally meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adulteresses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornicatresses"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The five animals, or living things, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayawaAnaAtu Alxamosu","text_ar":"الحَيَوَانَاتُ الخَمْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [specified voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAnN","text_ar":"حَيَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) are metaphorically termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAsiqu","text_ar":"فَوَاسِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Transgressors"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (Mgh, Msb) because of their noxiousness, (Mgh,) or because of their much, or frequent, noxiousness and harmfulness, so that they may be killed in the case of freedom from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in the state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", and in prayer, which is not rendered ineffectual thereby: (Msb:) or because of their being out of the pale of inviolability: or, as some [unreasonably] say, because the eating of them is forbidden. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K","IAar","S","Msb","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B3%D9%82/","headword_ar":"فاسق","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23456#f2cb04","body_html":"<span>الفاسق: من شهد ولم يعمل واعتقد.</span>"}]}}